I reviewed the metric, trace, and log analyses: persistent elevated socket KPIs across many services during the incident window and trace evidence pointing to checkoutservice as the most downstream faulty service in the call chain. This indicates a socket/connection-level failure impacting services, with checkoutservice being the primary affected component.

```json
{
    "1": {
        "root cause component": "checkoutservice",
        "root cause reason": "socket error"
    }
}
